## Avoid These Patterns
- Do not use class components
- Do not use inline styles (use Tailwind instead)
- Do not hardcode API keys in source code
- Do not use `var` for variable declarations
- Do not create separate CSS files (use Tailwind utilities)
- Do not use `any` type unless absolutely necessary

## Testing Considerations
- Components should be self-contained for easy testing
- API calls should be isolated in the services directory
- Use meaningful variable and function names for readability

## Git Commit Guidelines
- Use conventional commit format: `type: description`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `style`, `docs`, `chore`
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Write clear, descriptive commit messages
